title: Spare hours.
author: Brown, John
snippet: We are now past Carnwath, and got to that station which a shivering Cockney, who was kept waiting some hours on a windy winter night in the old shed, said was well-named Oarst airs (Carstairs), and past Thankerton, — Tancred's Town, — and Symington, — Symon's, — and are at Abington before nine.
